  "title": "Removal as Diagnostic Fallback",
  "concept": "When parallel exploration is too costly and a suspected source remains unproven, removing it forces clarity — either symptoms resolve or one major possibility is eliminated, reducing uncertainty at the cost of irreversibility.",
  "interactiveId": "18d76e80-9dcb-4cfa-926d-c5101f991415",
  "sourcePieceId": "b77e8406-a000-46ef-8989-dde9bb48a8b4",
  "publishedAt": 1777733277085,
  "voiceScore": 72,
  "qualityFlag": "low",
  "content": {
    "type": "html",
    "html": "<!DOCTYPE html>\n<html lang=\"en\">\n<head>\n<meta charset=\"utf-8\">\n<meta name=\"viewport\" content=\"width=device-width, initial-scale=1\">\n<title>Removal as Diagnostic Fallback</title>\n<style>\n  :root {\n    --bg: #faf7f1;\n    --fg: #1a1a1a;\n    --muted: #6b6b6b;\n    --line: #e5e0d6;\n    --gold: #c9a227;\n    --teal: #1a6b62;\n    --red: #c94c27;\n  }\n  * { box-sizing: border-box; }\n  body {\n    font-family: system-ui, -apple-system, \"Segoe UI\", sans-serif;\n    margin: 0;\n    padding: 20px;\n    color: var(--fg);\n    background: var(--bg);\n    line-height: 1.5;\n  }\n  h2 {\n    font-size: 1.05rem;\n    font-weight: 600;\n    margin: 0 0 4px;\n  }\n  p.subhead {\n    margin: 0 0 20px;\n    color: var(--muted);\n    font-size: 0.9rem;\n  }\n  .setup {\n    margin: 24px 0;\n    padding: 16px;\n    background: #fff;\n    border: 1px solid var(--line);\n    border-radius: 6px;\n  }\n  .setup-label {\n    font-size: 0.75rem;\n    color: var(--muted);\n    text-transform: uppercase;\n    letter-spacing: 0.06em;\n    margin-bottom: 10px;\n    font-weight: 500;\n  }\n  .toggles {\n    display: flex;\n    gap: 12px;\n    margin-bottom: 16px;\n  }\n  .toggle-btn {\n    flex: 1;\n    padding: 10px;\n    background: var(--line);\n    border: 2px solid var(--line);\n    border-radius: 4px;\n    font-size: 0.85rem;\n    font-weight: 500;\n    cursor: pointer;\n    transition: all 160ms;\n    text-align: center;\n  }\n  .toggle-btn.selected {\n    background: var(--teal);\n    border-color: var(--teal);\n    color: #fff;\n  }\n  .cost-display {\n    display: grid;\n    grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;\n    gap: 12px;\n    margin-bottom: 16px;\n  }\n  .cost-item {\n    padding: 10px;\n    background: var(--bg);\n    border-radius: 4px;\n  }\n  .cost-item-label {\n    font-size: 0.75rem;\n    color: var(--muted);\n    margin-bottom: 4px;\n  }\n  .cost-item-value {\n    font-weight: 600;\n    font-size: 1rem;\n  }\n  .slider-control {\n    margin-bottom: 16px;\n  }\n  .slider-control label {\n    display: block;\n    font-size: 0.85rem;\n    font-weight: 500;\n    margin-bottom: 8px;\n  }\n  .slider-wrapper {\n    display: flex;\n    align-items: center;\n    gap: 12px;\n  }\n  .slider-wrapper input[type=range] {\n    flex: 1;\n    accent-color: var(--teal);\n    min-width: 120px;\n  }\n  .slider-wrapper output {\n    font-variant-numeric: tabular-nums;\n    font-weight: 600;\n    min-width: 4ch;\n    text-align: right;\n  }\n  .pathway {\n    margin: 24px 0;\n    padding: 16px;\n    background: #fff;\n    border: 1px solid var(--line);\n    border-radius: 6px;\n  }\n  .pathway-status {\n    margin-bottom: 16px;\n    padding: 12px;\n    background: var(--bg);\n    border-radius: 4px;\n    font-size: 0.9rem;\n  }\n  .pathway-status-label {\n    font-size: 0.75rem;\n    color: var(--muted);\n    text-transform: uppercase;\n    letter-spacing: 0.06em;\n    margin-bottom: 4px;\n  }\n  .pathway-status-text {\n    font-weight: 500;\n  }\n  .actions {\n    display: flex;\n    gap: 10px;\n  }\n  button {\n    flex: 1;\n    padding: 11px 16px;\n    background: var(--teal);\n    color: #fff;\n    border: none;\n    border-radius: 4px;\n    font-size: 0.9rem;\n    font-weight: 500;\n    cursor: pointer;\n    transition: opacity 180ms;\n  }\n  button:hover:not(:disabled) {\n    opacity: 0.88;\n  }\n  button:disabled {\n    opacity: 0.35;\n    cursor: not-allowed;\n  }\n  button.remove {\n    background: var(--gold);\n  }\n  button.secondary {\n    background: var(--muted);\n  }\n  .outcome {\n    margin-top: 18px;\n    padding: 14px;\n    background: var(--bg);\n    border-radius: 4px;\n    font-size: 0.9rem;\n    display: none;\n  }\n  .outcome-label {\n    font-size: 0.75rem;\n    color: var(--muted);\n    text-transform: uppercase;\n    letter-spacing: 0.06em;\n    margin-bottom: 6px;\n  }\n  .outcome-text {\n    line-height: 1.6;\n  }\n  .outcome strong {\n    font-weight: 600;\n  }\n  p.caption {\n    margin: 14px 0 0;\n    color: var(--muted);\n    font-size: 0.875rem;\n  }\n  @media (max-width: 480px) {\n    .cost-display {\n      grid-template-columns: 1fr;\n    }\n    .actions {\n      flex-direction: column;\n    }\n  }\n</style>\n</head>\n<body>\n<h2>Set the constraint, then choose</h2>\n<p class=\"subhead\">Symptoms point to a suspected source. Exploring alternatives costs time and money. Removal is irreversible but forces clarity.</p>\n\n<div class=\"setup\">\n  <div class=\"setup-label\">True source (you see this; the system doesn't)</div>\n  <div class=\"toggles\">\n    <div class=\"toggle-btn selected\" data-source=\"suspected\" id=\"source-suspected\">Suspected source</div>\n    <div class=\"toggle-btn\" data-source=\"elsewhere\" id=\"source-elsewhere\">Elsewhere</div>\n  </div>\n  \n  <div class=\"slider-control\">\n    <label for=\"budget\">Exploration budget available:</label>\n    <div class=\"slider-wrapper\">\n      <input id=\"budget\" type=\"range\" min=\"0\" max=\"100\" value=\"30\" step=\"10\" aria-describedby=\"budget-out\">\n      <output id=\"budget-out\" for=\"budget\">30</output>\n    </div>\n  </div>\n  \n  <div class=\"cost-display\">\n    <div class=\"cost-item\">\n      <div class=\"cost-item-label\">Cost to explore one alternative</div>\n      <div class=\"cost-item-value\" id=\"explore-cost\">20</div>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"cost-item\">\n      <div class=\"cost-item-label\">Alternatives you can explore</div>\n      <div class=\"cost-item-value\" id=\"explore-count\">1</div>\n    </div>\n  </div>\n</div>\n\n<div class=\"pathway\">\n  <div class=\"pathway-status\">\n    <div class=\"pathway-status-label\">System state</div>\n    <div class=\"pathway-status-text\" id=\"status\">Ready. Budget allows limited exploration.</div>\n  </div>\n  \n  <div class=\"actions\">\n    <button id=\"explore-btn\">Explore One Alternative</button>\n    <button id=\"remove-btn\" class=\"remove\">Remove Suspected Source</button>\n    <button id=\"reset-btn\" class=\"secondary\">Reset</button>\n  </div>\n  \n  <div class=\"outcome\" id=\"outcome\">\n    <div class=\"outcome-label\">Outcome</div>\n    <div class=\"outcome-text\" id=\"outcome-text\"></div>\n  </div>\n</div>\n\n<p class=\"caption\" id=\"caption\">Parallel exploration is expensive. Each test consumes budget. Removal is irreversible but gives a definitive answer: either symptoms stop or one major possibility is ruled out.</p>\n\n<script>\n(function () {\n  var sourceSuspectedBtn = document.getElementById('source-suspected');\n  var sourceElsewhereBtn = document.getElementById('source-elsewhere');\n  var budgetSlider = document.getElementById('budget');\n  var budgetOut = document.getElementById('budget-out');\n  var exploreCostEl = document.getElementById('explore-cost');\n  var exploreCountEl = document.getElementById('explore-count');\n  var statusEl = document.getElementById('status');\n  var exploreBtn = document.getElementById('explore-btn');\n  var removeBtn = document.getElementById('remove-btn');\n  var resetBtn = document.getElementById('reset-btn');\n  var outcomeDiv = document.getElementById('outcome');\n  var outcomeText = document.getElementById('outcome-text');\n  var caption = document.getElementById('caption');\n  \n  var trueSource = 'suspected';\n  var budget = 30;\n  var exploreCost = 20;\n  var explored = 0;\n  var gameOver = false;\n  \n  function updateCounts() {\n    var canExplore = Math.floor(budget / exploreCost);\n    exploreCountEl.textContent = canExplore;\n    \n    if (gameOver) {\n      exploreBtn.disabled = true;\n      removeBtn.disabled = true;\n      return;\n    }\n    \n    if (canExplore > 0) {\n      exploreBtn.disabled = false;\n      statusEl.textContent = 'Budget allows ' + canExplore + ' exploration' + (canExplore === 1 ? '' : 's') + '. Each rules out one alternative but costs ' + exploreCost + '.';\n    } else {\n      exploreBtn.disabled = true;\n      if (explored === 0) {\n        statusEl.textContent = 'Budget too low to explore any alternatives. Removal is the only option.';\n      } else {\n        statusEl.textContent = 'Budget exhausted after ' + explored + ' exploration' + (explored === 1 ? '' : 's') + '. No alternatives ruled in. Removal remains.';\n      }\n    }\n  }\n  \n  function updateCaption() {\n    if (gameOver) {\n      if (trueSource === 'suspected') {\n        caption.textContent = 'Removal resolved the symptoms. The suspected source was correct. Irreversible action forced clarity.';\n      } else {\n        caption.textContent = 'Symptoms persist after removal. The suspected source was not the cause. One major possibility eliminated, but uncertainty remains.';\n      }\n    } else if (explored > 0) {\n      caption.textContent = 'Exploration ruled out ' + explored + ' alternative' + (explored === 1 ? '' : 's') + ' but found no match. Budget spent. Removal is now the fallback.';\n    } else {\n      caption.textContent = 'Parallel exploration is expensive. Each test consumes budget. Removal is irreversible but gives a definitive answer: either symptoms stop or one major possibility is ruled out.';\n    }\n  }\n  \n  sourceSuspectedBtn.addEventListener('click', function () {\n    if (gameOver) return;\n    trueSource = 'suspected';\n    sourceSuspectedBtn.classList.add('selected');\n    sourceElsewhereBtn.classList.remove('selected');\n  });\n  \n  sourceElsewhereBtn.addEventListener('click', function () {\n    if (gameOver) return;\n    trueSource = 'elsewhere';\n    sourceElsewhereBtn.classList.add('selected');\n    sourceSuspectedBtn.classList.remove('selected');\n  });\n  \n  budgetSlider.addEventListener('input', function () {\n    if (gameOver) return;\n    budget = +budgetSlider.value;\n    budgetOut.textContent = budget;\n    updateCounts();\n  });\n  \n  exploreBtn.addEventListener('click', function () {\n    if (gameOver) return;\n    var canExplore = Math.floor(budget / exploreCost);\n    if (canExplore === 0) return;\n    \n    budget -= exploreCost;\n    explored++;\n    budgetSlider.value = budget;\n    budgetOut.textContent = budget;\n    \n    statusEl.textContent = 'Explored one alternative. No match found. Budget remaining: ' + budget + '.';\n    \n    updateCounts();\n    updateCaption();\n  });\n  \n  removeBtn.addEventListener('click', function () {\n    if (gameOver) return;\n    \n    gameOver = true;\n    exploreBtn.disabled = true;\n    removeBtn.disabled = true;\n    sourceSuspectedBtn.style.pointerEvents = 'none';\n    sourceElsewhereBtn.style.pointerEvents = 'none';\n    budgetSlider.disabled = true;\n    \n    outcomeDiv.style.display = 'block';\n    \n    if (trueSource === 'suspected') {\n      outcomeText.innerHTML = '<strong>Symptoms stopped.</strong> Removal resolved the problem. The suspected source was the cause. Irreversible action forced clarity—uncertainty is gone.';\n      statusEl.textContent = 'Source removed. Symptoms resolved.';\n    } else {\n      outcomeText.innerHTML = '<strong>Symptoms persist.</strong> The suspected source was not the cause. One major possibility eliminated. Uncertainty reduced but not resolved—the true source lies elsewhere.';\n      statusEl.textContent = 'Source removed. Symptoms persist.';\n    }\n    \n    updateCaption();\n  });\n  \n  resetBtn.addEventListener('click', function () {\n    trueSource = 'suspected';\n    budget = 30;\n    explored = 0;\n    gameOver = false;\n    \n    sourceSuspectedBtn.classList.add('selected');\n    sourceElsewhereBtn.classList.remove('selected');\n    sourceSuspectedBtn.style.pointerEvents = '';\n    sourceElsewhereBtn.style.pointerEvents = '';\n    \n    budgetSlider.value = 30;\n    budgetSlider.disabled = false;\n    budgetOut.textContent = '30';\n    \n    outcomeDiv.style.display = 'none';\n    outcomeText.textContent = '';\n    \n    updateCounts();\n    updateCaption();\n  });\n  \n  updateCounts();\n  updateCaption();\n})();\n</script>\n</body>\n</html>"
  }
}
